description: This walk makes a loop around the surprisingly diverse wetlands, red gum forest, and rain forest
With an optional stretch of beach on the other side of the highway.

markers.description: Plan your drive to Toukley.
From the carpark at the veterans hostel, follow Evens Road to the trailhead.
Enter the wetlands past the gate on the right side of the bike path.

markers.title: Four Seasons in One Day: Wetlands
explanation: A short stretch of wetland makes a lush green welcome mat.
Once all of Central Coast was painted with the paints on this small pallete.
markers.description:
Visit this location to
earn the mystery trophy
After the wetlands turn right at the intersection, following the sign to the red gums walk.

markers.title: Four Seasons in One Day: Red Gum Forest
explanation: A streak of vivid red and orange across the sandy ridge.
Once all of Central Coast was painted with the paints on this small pallete.
markers.description:
Visit this location to
earn the mystery trophy
At the intersection follow the Lilly Pilly loop to the right.
From the shorefront, follow the Lilly Pilly loop to the left.

markers.title: Four Seasons in One Day: Rainforest
explanation: A green sky overhead as the rainforest covers the entire sky.
Once all of Central Coast was painted with the paints on this small pallete.
markers.description:
Visit this location to
earn the mystery trophy
On the left the Lilly Pilly Link trail offers a shortcut back that avoids the beach. -0.5h / 2km
The trail is somewhat overgrown, but still easy to follow.
At the intersection with the wider trail follow the Lilly Pilly Trail to the left.
At the next intersection follow the fainter Burrawang walking track to the right.
The trail ends intersecting with the Red Gum Trail. Follow it to the right to the carpark.
From the carpark follow the combined bike and footpath to the left back through the wetlands.
Follow the Lilly Pilly trail to the Central Coast Highway.
Follow the bike path along the highway to the left for a few hundred meters.
Or to avoid the traffic, use the service trail that runs parallel to it. +5m / 0km
Cross the highway at the carpark for the Pelican Beach Road.
Pass the gate at the carpark and follow the trail through the coast heath towards the ocean.
Cross the dunes across one of the trodden paths.
Follow the beach to the left towards Pelican Point.
Use the boardwalk across the dunes at the Pelican Beach carpark.
From the carpark follow Pelican Beach Road back to the Central Coast Highway.
To avoid the traffic along the highway follow the service trail to the left. +15m / 1km
Cross the highway at the carpark for the Red Gum Trail.
At intersection with the Central Coast Highway, look for the gap in the vegetation on the other side.
And cross the highway over to the wetlands bike path on the other side directly.
Follow the bike path to the right through the wetlands.
After the wetlands follow the bike path left past the veterans hostel.
The bike path ends back at the trailhead.
Plan your drive back from Toukley.
